HEADWORD: Yaw-weed
<hw>Yaw"-weed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
low, shrubby, rubiaceous plant (<spn>Morinda Royoc</spn>) growing along
the seacoast of the West Indies. It has small, white, odorous
flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

